This is, hands down, the worst Chipotle I have ever had the displeasure to order from. Back when I went into the location, the service was always glacial. Half of the staff is just standing around, those that are working are moving at a snail's pace, and multiple times I've witness workers letting their friends cut the line in order to get food that they then don't pay for. The portions you get here are almost half of what you get when you go to other Chipotle locations. I live a 5 minute walk from this location and now that I've been ordering online for delivery, the portions are just as small but now they always mess it up and it's always ice cold by the time it arrives. Also, many times it takes 45 minutes to get my order, and it's not the driver's fault. The time between when the driver picks it up to when it is delivered is only a few minutes. If you can go to any other Chipotle, do so.

You do not want to go to this location OR order anything online during COVID.  I went this week to order a to go order in person.  There are signs on the door saying face masks are mandatory.  However, the workers were mostly not wearing them or would start to put one on only when I made eye contact.  The young lady making my burrito had a mask but it kept falling down.  So, while she was making my food and her hands had gloves, she touched her nose area to pull the mask back up.  Then went immediately back to touching my food.  The young man who was cashier for my order never once wore a mask even though we was basically right in my face when he took my credit card.  I also saw him making the delivery orders with no mask at ALL.  I felt really bad for the people who would receive those orders as they have no idea someone was standing right above their food breathing and such with no mask.  This location needs to be shut down during COVID.

I try to give this location a chance to redeem themselves but unfortunately this location doesn’t know how to follow directions on an online order. I placed an order today for pick-up, I check for my food and they forgot my burrito. They were able to fix it right away. What I should’ve done was checked my bowl and they completely messed it up: I ordered vegetarian and they put chicken, I ask for guacamole on the side for my bowl they put a chuck load of guacamole inside the bowl. If you have a car, please go to the next chipotle and not to this location. If you place an online order please check your order is correct and accurate.
